verses.roman:
bhojana kari' nityānanda ācamana kailā
cāri kuṇḍīra avaśeṣa raghunāthe dilā

synonyms: bhojana kari'-after finishing eating; nityānanda—Nityānanda Prabhu; ācamana kailā—washing His hands and mouth; cāri kuṇḍīra—of the four pots; avaśeṣa—what was remaining; raghunāthe dilā—delivered to Raghunātha dāsa.
translation: After Lord Nityānanda Prabhu finished eating, He washed His hands and mouth and gave Raghunātha dāsa the food remaining in the four pots.
